Interface Kind2<TYPE extends Kind2<TYPE,?,?>,T1,T2>

  • Type Parameters:
    TYPE - The recursive type described by Kind2
    T1 - The first component type of TYPE
    T2 - The second component type of TYPE

    public interface Kind2<TYPE extends Kind2<TYPE,?,?>,T1,T2>
    Recursive self type representing TYPE<T1, T2>, which allows similar behavior to higher-kinded types.
    Since:
    2.0.0
    Author:
    Daniel Dietrich, Eric Nelson
